derivation.yuyuan_name: Old English  bodian 'proclaim, foretell', from boda 'messenger', of Germanic origin; related to German Bote, also to bid

entry.tran: 预示（好事或坏事）；是…的兆头
entry.def: If something bodes ill, it makes you think that something bad will happen in the future. If something bodes well, it makes you think that something good will happen.

example.ex: She says the way the bill was passed bodes ill for democracy...
example.tran: 她说，从该法案被通过的情形来看，民主的前景惨淡。

example.ex: Grace had dried her eyes. That boded well.
example.tran: 格雷丝已擦干了眼泪，应该没事了。
